    <description>The amount of opioid medication used was recorded. Then, it was converted to morphine equivalents (https://www.cms.gov/Medicare/Prescription-Drug-Coverage/PrescriptionDrugCovContra/Downloads/Opioid-Morphine-EQ-Conversion-Factors-March-2015.pdf). Opioid use was measured over a 2-week baseline period. Then, the average opioid medication use/week was calculated. This was compared to the average opioid medication use/week after 4 weeks of NAC.</description>
